            "title": "OpenAI acquires Astral to bolster its Codex programming assistant",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text article-text--clear\"><p>This acquisition comes at a time of rapid adoption for AI-driven programming assistants. OpenAI reports that Codex now has over 2 million weekly active users, with its user base tripling since the beginning of the year. The company is seeking to solidify its position against rivals such as Anthropic and Cursor.<br/><br/>The deal remains subject to customary regulatory approvals and is part of a broader acquisition strategy. OpenAI has recently ramped up its buyouts, including the $6.4bn acquisition of startup io, as well as Promptfoo in cybersecurity and Torch in healthcare. The hiring of former Google executive Albert Lee to lead the external development strategy confirms this expansionist drive.</p></div>",
