            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text article-text--clear\"><p>The company indicated that the permitting procedures are expected to begin between late 2025 and early 2026. The project notably includes the construction of a concentrator plant as well as a desalination unit, designed to secure water supply in an arid region. This infrastructure is intended to significantly increase the site's production capacity.<br/><br/>The new facilities are expected to come online within the next decade. This development comes amid rising demand for copper, a metal essential to the energy transition and electrical technologies, reinforcing the interest of major mining groups in expanding their capacities.<br/><br/>Freeport-McMoRan shares are tumbling 6.5% in early trading on Wall Street.</p></div>",
